  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc8\u0baf \u0bb5\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8 ! \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b85\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b85\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb2\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bcd !",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Today's weather! Sea waves may increase!",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Department of Meteorology has said that the Sabaragamuwa province and Nuwara Eliya and Kandy districts will experience several spells of rain.",
        "It is expected that strong winds of 40-50 kmph may blow from time to time in the western slopes of the central hill country and the southern province.",
        "Light rain is expected over coastal areas from Puttalam through Colombo and Galle to Matara.",
        "Wind will be from West to South-West direction with wind speed of 20-35 kmph. The wind speed is expected to increase to 45-55 kmph in coastal areas from Puttalam to Pottuvil through Colombo, Galle and Ambantota.",
        "The sea surface from Puttalam through Colombo, Galle and Ambantota to Pottuvil is turbulent. Other seas surrounding the country are expected to be moderate.",
        "Waves (around 2.0 \u2013 2.5 m) are expected in offshore areas from Puttalam through Colombo, Galle and Ambantota to Pottuvil.",
        "Mariners and fishing communities have been advised to exercise caution while visiting the above seas."
      ],
